From 1787979ee582890ac6f3d99bc9255f6b5129023d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alok Singh <aloksing@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Mon, 30 Jun 2025 23:08:04 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM: DP: wifi: ath12k: Refactor monitor hal specific
 functions

monitor hal tlv processing is currently part of ath12k/dp_mon.c
(ath12k.ko common module) with the Unified Driver framework,
monitor hal tlv processing logic is being move to the
architecture-specific file.

Move wifi7 specific monitor TLV parsing APIs to wifi7/hal_mon.c
Defines operations (hal_ops) to handle WiFi7 and WiFi8(upcoming chipsets)
parsing separately to allow chipset-specific parsing variations,
since monitor TLV formats differ between WiFi7 and upcoming WiFi8.
Add hal_mon_qcn9274.c and hal_mon_wcn7850.c new files for handling
chipset specific wifi7 operations.

Patch-dependency:
	0403-0001-UPSTREAM-DP-wifi-ath12k-Refactor-monitor-hal-specifi.patch

Signed-off-by: Alok Singh <aloksing@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
